# Exploration: xargs

## Test scope
  170 behavioral groups: 67 unique, 103 shared

## Observed: 18/21 flags
  7 uniquely observable, 11 distinguishable via flag pairs
  2 error-only (flag recognized but no successful output observed)
  robustness: 23 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

Aliases: -0 = --null, -L = --max-lines, -P = --max-procs, -a = --arg-file, -d = --delimiter, -n = --max-args, -o = --open-tty, -p = --interactive, -r = --no-run-if-empty, -s = --max-chars, -t = --verbose, -x = --exit

## Unique behavior (observable when tested alone)
  --show-limits  # show limits on command-line length
    tested: "--show-limits" in words_minimal / stdin
    | stderr: Your environment variables take up 23044 bytes
    without flag:
      cherry apple banana
    with flag:
      cherry apple banana
  -L  # use at most MAX-LINES non-blank input lines per command line
    tested: "-L" "2" "echo" "input.txt" in passwd_minimal / stdin
    | flag adds 2 lines: input.txt a,b,c d:e:f, input.txt g h i
    | flag removes 1 lines: input.txt a,b,c d:e:f g h i
    without flag:
      input.txt a,b,c d:e:f g h i
    with flag:
      input.txt a,b,c d:e:f
      input.txt g h i
  -a  # read arguments from FILE, not standard input
    tested: "--arg-file=other.txt" "echo" "input.txt" in words_minimal
    | flag adds 1 lines: input.txt hello world
    | flag removes 1 lines: input.txt
    without flag:
      input.txt
    with flag:
      input.txt hello world
  -n  # use at most MAX-ARGS arguments per command line
    tested: "-n" "2" "echo" "input.txt" in passwd_minimal / stdin
    | flag adds 3 lines: input.txt a,b,c d:e:f, input.txt g h, input.txt i
    | flag removes 1 lines: input.txt a,b,c d:e:f g h i
    without flag:
      input.txt a,b,c d:e:f g h i
    with flag:
      input.txt a,b,c d:e:f
      input.txt g h
      input.txt i
  -o  # Reopen stdin as /dev/tty in the child process before executing the command
    tested: "-o" in passwd_deep
    | flag removes 1 lines: 
    | exit: 0 → 125
    | stderr: xargs: '/dev/tty': No such device or address
  -r  # if there are no arguments, then do not run COMMAND
    tested: "-r" in passwd_standard
    | flag removes 1 lines: 
  -s  # limit length of command line to MAX-CHARS
    tested: "-s" "1" in passwd_standard
    | flag removes 1 lines: 
    | exit: 0 → 1
    | stderr: xargs: option requires an argument -- 's'
  -t  # print commands before executing them
    tested: "-t" in words_minimal / stdin
    | stderr: /nix/store/n9gh8gxx5xx51ihgll2l20ar9b2vmgzy-coreutils-9.5/bin/echo cherry apple banana
    without flag:
      cherry apple banana
    with flag:
      cherry apple banana

